#
def cat_judFunct(cat_name,List=oneHot_list):
    i=0
    for name in List:
        if cat_name == name:
            i+=1
    if i ==1:
        return True
    else:
        return False

In [96]:
#keyvalue//
def drop_self_cor(corr_df,targetName,thr):
    rslt_dict={}
    for colname in corr_df.columns:
        if (colname == targetName):
            continue
        else:
            tmpt = corr_df[[colname,targetName]][abs(corr_df[colname])>=thr]
            if len(tmpt)>1:#
                drop_List = list(tmpt.index)
                keep_col = tmpt[tmpt[targetName]==tmpt[targetName].max()].index[0]
                drop_List.remove(keep_col)
                rslt_dict[keep_col] = drop_List
    return rslt_dict

#0-1
def Stander_01(df):
    dataframe = df.copy()
    for colName in dataframe.columns:
        minval= dataframe[colName].min()
        maxval= dataframe[colName].max()
        gapval= maxval-minval
        dataframe[colName] = (dataframe[colName]-minval)/gapval
    return dataframe
X_train = Stander_01(X_train)
X_test = Stander_01(X_test)
In [108]:
#
def Model_Evaluate(pred_data,real_data): #pred_data,real_datanp.arraynp.exm1
    Ape_arry=abs((pred_data-real_data)/real_data)
    Mape = np.mean(Ape_arry)
    Accuracy5_count=0
    for Ape in Ape_arry:
        if(Ape<=0.05):
            Accuracy5_count+=1
    Accuracy5 = Accuracy5_count/len(Ape_arry)
    indicator = 0.2*(1-Mape)+0.8*Accuracy5
    return indicator,Accuracy5,Mape

In [147]:
#:MAE
def myFeval(preds, xgbtrain):
    label = xgbtrain.get_label()
    score = mean_absolute_error(np.expm1(label), np.expm1(preds))
    return 'myFeval', score, False

In [152]:
for fold_, (trn_idx, val_idx) in enumerate(folds.split(X_data, Y_data)):
    print("fold n{}".format(fold_ + 1))
    trn_data = lgb.Dataset(X_data[trn_idx], Y_data[trn_idx])
    val_data = lgb.Dataset(X_data[val_idx], Y_data[val_idx])

    num_round = 100000000
    clf = lgb.train(param, trn_data, num_round, valid_sets=[trn_data, val_data], verbose_eval=300,
                    early_stopping_rounds=600, feval = myFeval)
    oof_lgb[val_idx] = clf.predict(X_data[val_idx], num_iteration=clf.best_iteration)
    predictions_lgb += clf.predict(X_data_test, num_iteration=clf.best_iteration) / folds.n_splits
    predictions_train_lgb += clf.predict(X_data, num_iteration=clf.best_iteration) / folds.n_splits

02 catBoost¶

In [160]:
kfolder = KFold(n_splits=10, shuffle=True, random_state=2018)
oof_cb = np.zeros(len(X_data))
predictions_cb = np.zeros(len(X_data_test))
predictions_train_cb = np.zeros(len(X_data))
kfold = kfolder.split(X_data, Y_data)
fold_ = 0
In [161]:
for train_index, vali_index in kfold:
    fold_ = fold_ + 1
    print("fold n{}".format(fold_))
    k_x_train = X_data[train_index]
    k_y_train = Y_data[train_index]
    k_x_vali = X_data[vali_index]
    k_y_vali = Y_data[vali_index]
    cb_params = {
        'n_estimators': 100000000,
        'loss_function': 'MAE',
        'eval_metric': 'MAE',
        'learning_rate': 0.01,
        'depth': 6,
        'use_best_model': True,
        'subsample': 0.6,
        'bootstrap_type': 'Bernoulli',
        'reg_lambda': 3,
        'one_hot_max_size': 2,
    }
    model_cb = CatBoostRegressor(**cb_params)
    # train the model
    model_cb.fit(k_x_train, k_y_train, eval_set=[(k_x_vali, k_y_vali)], verbose=300, early_stopping_rounds=600)
    oof_cb[vali_index] = model_cb.predict(k_x_vali, ntree_end=model_cb.best_iteration_)
    predictions_cb += model_cb.predict(X_data_test, ntree_end=model_cb.best_iteration_) / kfolder.n_splits
    predictions_train_cb += model_cb.predict(X_data, ntree_end=model_cb.best_iteration_) / kfolder.n_splits
